hkhk - Chinese, Australian Foreign Ministers Meet in Hong Kong 
Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met with
Australian Foreign Minister Alexander Downer at the Hong Kong
Convention and Exhibition Center here this morning.
Downer is here to attend the Sino-British Hong Kong handover ceremony
at midnight today.
Downer congratulated Qian on the upcoming return of Hong Kong to China,
and said that he was very glad to be able to meet with Qian at this
historic moment.
The return of Hong Kong is a significant event for Hong Kong, China,
and the entire Asia-Pacific region, he said.
Qian said that he was also very pleased to meet with Downer again in
Hong Kong.
Earlier today, Qian had met respectively with Portuguese Foreign
Minister Jaime Gama, British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook, U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright and Japanese Foreign Minister
Yukihiko Ikeda. He will also meet with Russian Foreign Minister Y.M.
Primakov and German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel this morning.
